    "treatments": "Treatment for angina pectoris aims to relieve symptoms, improve quality of life, and prevent heart attacks. Medications are commonly prescribed: nitrates help relax blood vessels, beta-blockers reduce heart workload, anticoagulants prevent blood clots, and statins lower cholesterol. Lifestyle modifications such as a heart-healthy diet, regular exercise, quitting smoking, and stress management are vital. In some cases, procedures like angioplasty or coronary artery bypass graft surgery may be necessary to improve blood flow to the heart. Continuous monitoring and follow-up care are crucial to managing the condition effectively."
